04 Feb 2022
common directories
/etc
- common place to store system files used by the operating system
- holds files like passwd and shadow files
 -- shows how your system stores the passwords for each user in encryption format
  -- encryption format is sha512

/var
- stores data that is fequently accessed or written by services or applications running on the system

/root
-home directory for root user
- this user will have their data in a directory like /home/root

/tmp
- tmp short for temporary
- volatile
- is used to store data that is needed to be access once or twice
- when the computer is restarted this folder is cleared out
- for pentration testing 
 --any user can write to this folder
 -- a good place to store enumenration scripts
 
